    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a directed network graph with 6 nodes (continents) and 15 weighted edges (trade relationships). Synthetic trade volumes follow a log-normal distribution (\u03bc=1.9, \u03c3=0.7) to simulate real-world economic interactions where most transactions are moderate-sized with occasional large deals. The dependency wheel visualization was chosen for its ability to show reciprocal relationships through chord curvature while maintaining Tufte's data-ink ratio by eliminating gridlines. Cairo's perceptual principles are applied through: 1) Position encoding for continent nodes 2) Hue differentiation for trade directions 3) Width-based weight representation. Color saturation reinforces weight perception, with the green-blue-purple spectrum providing adequate luminance contrast against the dark theme while maintaining colorblind accessibility."
